                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-17T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 17, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 17—9:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2016. Waterman’s 13 of September 16, 10 a.m.<note n="26" xml:id="d644fn26">Not
                        printed; Henry S. Waterman, Consul at Bordeaux, had reported that French
                        authorities intended to remove enemy nationals from crews of American ships
                        (340.1115A/2).</note> regarding enemy aliens included in the crews of
                    American ships. I have informed Waterman as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Embassy has no intention of intervening in behalf of enemy aliens
                            included in the crews of American ships and the Department has been so
                            informed. I desire that you take no action in this respect without prior
                            consultation with the Embassy.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
